  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this became a kind of a visible thing on, on campus.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Were you involved in any other activities of note in college?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was a member of a, a fraternity, Phi Gamma Delta.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was kind of known as the special liberal in that house, in that fraternity house, most of whom were quite wealthy, including Fred Maytag, the maker of the washing machines, and Bill Vilter, the maker of the machines which are used to cool, were used to cool theaters 40 years ago, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I immediately went to the University of London and attended the London School of Economics and Political Science for one year.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I was not seeking a degree, so I spent about a third of my time traveling on the continent of Europe.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1934, beginning in September and lasting until about August of the next year.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I traveled throughout Europe, throughout the northern part of Europe, to Holland and France, Nazi Germany-- I spent over three or four weeks in Nazi Germany altogether-- Switzerland, Poland, Soviet Russia, Sweden, where I had an interview with the prime minister of Sweden when I was 22 years old, Norway, Scotland, Great Britain.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went to Hyde Park early in my years at the university, at the London School of Economics, to attend, not as a participant, but as a boor, an onlooker, a meeting that was being held by Sir Oswald Mosley, M-O-S-L-E-Y, who was the head of the British fascists.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so I was with this group of students and other British people, mainly, who were booing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were separated from this demonstration, this meeting which they were having in Hyde Park, by police.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
